                                "text": "Typically, if the viewport is showing 1\/10th of the document, the thumb takes up 1\/10th of the scroll bar; if 1\/100th, 1\/100th. At that point, the thumb is so small, it’s a bad UI experience — hard to see, hard to click on.\n\nRather, the reduction should be logarithmic, so that even at 1\/1000th, the thumb is smaller, but still usable."
